 her on-the-ground fieldwork provide incredibly valuable and accurate first-hand documentation of the tactics of some of the world’s most notorious insurgent groups. Inside Insurgency offers the reader a timely and intimate understanding of these movements, and explains the changing behavior of insurgent groups toward the civilians they claim to represent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aInsurgency. 0aPolitical violence. 0aViolence. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aInside.  aInsurgency.  abehavior.  achanging.  acivilians.  aclaim.  aexplains.  agroups.  ainsurgent.  aintimate.  amovements.  aoffers.  areader.  arepresent.  athese.  athey.  atimely.  atoward.  aunderstanding.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081479577440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814795774.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814759554423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814759554/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK